Package GraphCreation

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GeneratedGraph
    Blanket interface to help identify graphs that were generated instead of loaded externally
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BarabasiAlbertGraphGenerator
    Graph Generator using the BarabasiAlbert model.
    BasicGraph
    A class that allows for importing and exporting of any type of graph, using build in JUNG export/import functionality NOTE: The edges of this graph will not match, since vertex and edge ids will not be the same.
    ErdosRenyiGraphGenerator
    Graph Generator that creates a random graph using the Erdos-Renyi binomial model (each pair of vertices is connected with probability p) This does not support DIRECTED graphs and wraps the JUNG ErdosRenyiGenerator Functionality
    FriendsTwitterDataImporter
    The purpose of this class is to be able import in the Twitter data (friends.csv) and convert it to a JUNG graph.
    GraphLoader
    This abstract class is for all the classes used to generate graphs from all the data sets.
    ImportedGraph
    Abstraction on a normal graph loader that the path is a graph already exists
    VertexTVertexImporter
    Class for importing graphs that are composed of edges separated by a split.
